(thirdQuint)Determining the Amount of Time Needed for Nelfinavir to Boost the Immune System in Adults.

 Blood will be collected at several time points during the study.

 DNA will be isolated from peripheral blood lymphocytes (PBL) and assessed for signal point (sj) TREC content relative to genomic CCR5 copies by real time PCR in a spectoflourometic thermal cycler.

 TREC values will be expressed as TREC copy number per copies of CCR5 or TREC/PBLs.

 We anticipate that we will confirm our previous observations that nelfinavir therapy will increase TRECs, indicating naive T cell production from the thymus.

 The proposed study will determine the time course of the anticipated increase in TREC/PBLs.

